## 🔴 Upgrade Confusion: "I Didn't Get the Tokens I Expected"

### The Upgrade Math (Surprises Many Users)
**Scenario**: User on Starter (1M) upgrades to Personal (5M)
- Starter tokens are **replaced**, NOT added
- If they used 600K starter tokens, they get: 5M - 600K = **4.4M Personal tokens**
- NOT 5M + remaining starter = 6M (this is the common wrong expectation)

**Scenario**: User on Personal (5M) upgrades to Rocket (10.5M mid-cycle)
- Prorated charge for remaining days
- Gets full Rocket allocation minus already-used Personal tokens
- Example: Used 3M of 5M Personal → gets **7.5M tokens instantly**

### What to Tell Users
"When you upgrade, your balance moves to the new plan's full allocation minus what you've already used. Starter tokens are replaced by the paid plan — they don't stack on top. The good news is you immediately get access to the higher plan's token pool."

