## Refuel Tokens
- $20 = 5M tokens per pack
- Buy multiple packs if needed
- Don't expire while subscription is active
- **When to recommend refuel vs upgrade**:

| Situation | Recommendation |
|---|---|
| Finishing current project, won't need more soon | Refuel |
| Running out of tokens every month | Upgrade plan |
| On 2nd+ refuel this billing cycle | Upgrade (better value) |
| Mid-project, unexpected scope increase | Refuel |

---

## Cancellation — What Users Lose
When a user cancels their subscription:
- ALL tokens (subscription + bonus + refuel) expire at billing cycle end
- Projects and code remain accessible indefinitely
- Cannot generate new code once tokens are zero
- Private visibility on projects may revert to public

**Always tell users before they cancel**: "Your code and projects stay accessible forever. But any unused tokens expire when your billing period ends. If you've got tokens left, use them before cancelling — or download your code first."

---

## Token Refund Policy
- Tokens consumed in failed/broken generations: generally NOT auto-refunded
- Tokens consumed in rolled-back versions: NOT refunded
- **Fix It feature**: Free for paid users — no tokens consumed for Fix It
- **Goodwill exceptions**: Support team can add bonus tokens for genuine platform failures — escalate to team with full context

---

## Annual Plan Gotcha (Warn Users Near Renewal)
At annual renewal:
- ALL unused tokens from the year **expire immediately**
- Fresh 12-month balance starts
- Unlike monthly plans, there's no indefinite rollover

Tip: Remind annual subscribers 2 weeks before renewal to use up remaining tokens.

