## Common Billing Q&A

**Q: "My tokens expired — when does my plan reset?"**
A: Paid monthly plans reset on your billing date each month. You can check this in Settings → Subscription.

**Q: "I cancelled — when do tokens expire?"**
A: At the END of your current billing cycle, not immediately.

**Q: "I upgraded mid-month, what was I charged?"**
A: A prorated charge for remaining days on the new plan, minus a credit for unused days on the old plan.

**Q: "Why didn't my tokens go up when I upgraded from Starter?"**
A: Starter tokens are replaced by the paid plan — not added. You get the paid plan's full allocation minus what you'd already used from Starter.

**Q: "Can I get a refund?"**
A: Escalate to team. Rocket has offered goodwill refunds in cases of platform failure. Not guaranteed but worth escalating for paying customers.

**Q: "Do refuel tokens expire if I downgrade?"**
A: Refuel tokens expire if you CANCEL. Downgrading is different — refuel tokens remain until cancellation.

